{"id": "duc04-testb-27:0#0", "contents": "China has officially approved the use of the euro in trade and financial transactions, effective January 1. This announcement was made by the People's Bank of China and the State Administration of Foreign Exchange, as reported by the Xinhua News Agency. The authorization allows financial institutions, enterprises, and individuals in China to accept and use the euro in economic, trade, and financial exchanges with the 11 member countries of the European Union. Additionally, they can convert, use, and open euro accounts."}
